Katja and Claudia, both recovered from eating disorders, opened Germany's first restaurant for anorexics and bulimics.
Claudia, wearing a white chef's hat, uses her culinary skills to help those struggling with similar issues.
The restaurant provides a safe space for individuals transitioning to a normal life.
Meanwhile, in Italy, TV ads targeting children with food products are linked to eating disorders.
Researchers are exploring the role of leptin in restoring menstrual periods in female athletes with low body fat.
The battle against eating disorders continues, with challenges in treatment accessibility and societal perceptions.
